comments: She is the best teacher! Very helpful and friendly. I will miss her

Biagiotti is great! I loved her as a teacher, she\'s done a lot of different things in the science community so she knows a lot of different things about science in general. She was awesome and had a personal connection with most students.
She\'s the best teacher you can ever have for a Biology class. Very sweet and nice, can be a little dorky and goofy. She tries to make the class fun! And very enthusiastic...TAKE HER!
This class was easy shes very nice take her if you need help ask her shes very helpful

She teaches all the material that will be on the test. You really only need the text book if you missed a class or if you\'re having a hard time understanding a concept. There are only a few assignments and the tests are straight forward. Just show up and do the work.
Great teacher, she works with the class and goes through the power points trying to answer any questions. Does a great job of explaining things. I highly suggest her.
Nice teacher that cares for her students a great deal. She gives you a review packet that covers everything that will be on the Exams usually a week or two before.

Ms. Biagiotti is one of the nicest teachers on campus. She was a pleasure to have this semester. I just wished I had done better in her class than I did, but that blizzard week really threw me off. Oh well, I can\'t fight with Mother Nature. Other than that, try her out, you will love her.
not hard nor easy, i just dont like the reading she gives us before exams. overall shes good
She made it easy and fun!

Terrible. Moves too quickly, the book used for the class is AWFUL they say that they created it to make it easier when it just hinders you learning. She goes WAY too quickly, people in my LAB class agreed and said they had stopped going to her class because they werent learning anything. It is hard to pay attention to her.

Professor Biagiotti is one of the best professors i have had. She explains everything clearly,and moves at your pace. She offers help after her classes, and includes eye catching pictures and examples in her powerpoints. If you haven\'t taken Bio-101 yet, take her! She\'s the best.

She is extremely nice and easy to understand. Goes into great detail for difficult topics. Adds extra cool things during lecture to keep you as interested and amazed about the subject of biology as she is. She is wonderful. Her tests are fairly simple, if you go to class and pay attention you\'ll get an A
Had her for Microbio Lab and she was awesome!! Very Helpful and her materia was not hard to follow. Would recommend for Lab.
Great at explaining. Hands out review packet for tests. Straight foward. You come to class, and put in effort, you get an A.
